ul feature, especially for evening sessions where overtrading is the main risk.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Promote **churn regime** as a real alpha-pipeline candidate for PM confidence scoring.\n- Working definition: if both YES and NO are sitting in the **0.495-0.505 band**, treat that as a hard no-trade regime unless another independently validated feature overrides it.\n- This should complement, not replace, the evening bias and V5b filters.\n\n**Next:** Convert this into a deployable spec or patch candidate: add an explicit churn filter to the evening session logic, then backtest whether combining `churn block + evening bias >= 55 + weak-tag block` further improves expectancy over the current leading candidate.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-21 19:46 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] 19h Churn Confirms the Real Edge Is Doing Nothing\n\n**Task:** Use the now-complete live 19h tape to test whether the evening strategy candidate still holds up after a full session of real observations, not just an early-window sample.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive and the PM bot is beh",
